fr.sii.ogham.email.builder

Class AutofillEmailBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.AbstractParent<EmailBuilder>
      • fr.sii.ogham.email.builder.AutofillEmailBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Builder<MessageFiller>, Parent<EmailBuilder>

    public class AutofillEmailBuilder
extends AbstractParent<EmailBuilder>
implements Builder<MessageFiller>
    Configures how Ogham will add default values to the Email if some information is missing. If sender address is missing, a default one can be defined in configuration properties. If recipient address is missing, a default one can be defined in configuration properties. If subject is missing, a default one can be defined either:
    • In HTML title
    • In first line of text template
    • Using a default value defined in configuration properties

    • Method Detail

      • subject

        public AutofillSubjectBuilder subject()
        Configures how to handle missing Email subject: if no subject is explicitly defined on the Email, Ogham will use the result of this builder configuration to provide a default subject. Default subject can be provided by:
        • Using HTML <title> header tag as subject
        • Using first line text if prefixed
        • Using a property value
        Returns:
        the builder to configure default subject handling
